value.name: Lambda Herculis - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Lambda Herculis (λ Herculis. abbreviated Lambda Her, λ Her), formally named Maasym / ˈ m eɪ ə s ɪ m /, is a star in the constellation of Hercules. From parallax measurements taken during the Gaia mission, it is approximately 393 light-years from the Sun .

value.name: Hercules Constellation: Stars, Myth, Facts, Location ...
value.snippet: Lambda Herculis has the stellar classification K3.5III. It has an apparent magnitude of 4.402 and is approximately 370 light years distant from the solar system. English astronomer William Herschel discovered that the solar system as a whole was moving in the direction that was close to the location of Lambda Herculis in the sky.

value.name: Omicron Herculis - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Omicron Herculis, Latinized from o Herculis, is a star in the constellation Hercules. It used to be called Masym ("the wrist"), but this name was transferred to Lambda Herculis. Properties. Omicron Herculis is a B9.5III star approximately 106 pc from the Earth. It has an apparent magnitude of 3.83.

value.snippet: Beta Herculis is a binary star system consisting of Kornephoros, a yellow giant of the spectral type G7 IIIa, and a close companion. value.name: Tau Herculis - University Of Illinois Urbana-Champaign
value.snippet: TAU HER (Tau Herculis). Rather far off the Milky Way for a hot class B star (a B5 subgiant, but see below), Tau Herculis is Hercules ' most northerly Greek-letter-named star, beating Iota Her by just over a quarter of a degree, although at fourth magnitude (3.89) it does not make much of an impact on the constellation.

value.name: Lambda Herculis - frwiki.wiki
value.snippet: Lambda Herculis (λ Herculis, zkráceně λ Jí), také volal Maasym, je hvězda v souhvězdí of Hercules. Je to asi 385 světelných let od Země. Tradiční jména. Nese tradiční název Maasym, což znamená „zápěstí“.
